This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques applied to clinical text data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses unsupervised learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which are relevant to the cs.IR and cs.AI categories, respectively. Finally, the paper deals with clinical data, which could be relevant to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) category, which deals with the social and ethical implications of computing.
